# Color and Text Styling Guidelines

## Color Usage
- **Single Source of Truth**: All colors must come from variables defined in [src/styles/colors.css](mdc:src/styles/colors.css)
- **Never use hardcoded color values** (like hex codes or rgb values) anywhere in the codebase
- **Direct CSS variable usage is now required** since tailwind color classes have been removed
  ```tsx
  /* Best practice - use direct CSS variables */
  <div className="text-[var(--text-primary)] bg-[var(--bg-secondary)] border-[var(--border-default)]">Content</div>
  
  /* Incorrect - hardcoded values */
  <div style={{ 
    color: '#ffffff', 
    backgroundColor: '#353535',
    borderColor: '#464646'
  }}>Content</div>
  ```
- **For CSS styling**, always use CSS variables:
  ```css
  /* Correct */
  .custom-element {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background-color: var(--bg-secondary);
  }
  
  /* Incorrect */
  .custom-element {
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #353535;
  }
  ```
- **Choose semantic color variables** when available:
  ```tsx
  /* Correct */
  <span className="text-[var(--blue-text)]">Blue text</span>
  <button className="bg-[var(--green-bg)] text-[var(--text-primary)]">Success</button>
  <div className="bg-[var(--red-bg-hover)]">Hover state</div>
  
  /* Incorrect */
  <span className="text-[#8AC2FF]">Blue text</span>
  <button style={{backgroundColor: '#00a457', color: '#ffffff'}}>Success</button>
  ```
- **For special cases** like gradients, use CSS variables from colors.css:
  ```css
  /* Correct */
  .custom-element {
    background: linear-gradient(var(--blue-bg), var(--blue-bg-hover));
  }
  
  /* Incorrect */
  .custom-element {
    background: linear-gradient(#0084FF, #2496FF);
  }
  ```
- **Utility classes** in [src/styles/colors.css](mdc:src/styles/colors.css) can also be used:
  ```tsx
  /* Utility classes (alternative approach) */
  <div className="color-text-primary color-bg-secondary">Content</div>
  <span className="color-blue-text">Blue text</span>
  ```

## Text Styling
- Use text styling classes from [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- The predominant text styles to use are:
  - `body-text` - For standard text content
  - `body-semibold` - For emphasized body text
  - `title-text` - For regular titles
  - `title-semibold` - For emphasized titles
- Example implementation:
  ```tsx
  /* Correct */
  <p className="body-text">Regular text content</p>
  <h3 className="title-semibold">Section Title</h3>
  
  /* Avoid inline styles */
  <p style={{fontSize: '0.72rem', lineHeight: '16px'}}>Text content</p>
  ```
- Maintain consistent typography across components by using these predefined classes
- Only deviate from these styles when explicitly needed for special UI elements

## Dark Mode Compatibility
- All color usage should work properly in both light and dark modes
- Test color contrast in both modes to ensure accessibility

## Theme Variables
- Theme variables defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) map to the appropriate color variables depending on the current theme
- Access these via CSS variables:
  ```tsx
  /* Theme-aware styling */
  <div className="bg-[var(--card)] text-[var(--card-foreground)]">Card content</div>
  <button className="bg-[var(--primary)] text-[var(--primary-foreground)]">Primary button</button>
  <div style={{ borderColor: 'var(--destructive)' }}>Error container</div>
  ```
